  "prompt": "What is the best online school for design?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" online school for design can be subjective and dependent on your specific needs, preferences, and career goals. However, several reputable institutions consistently rank highly and offer comprehensive design programs online. Here are some top choices:\n\n1. **Rhode Island School of Design (RISD) Continuing Education**: Offers a range of online courses in design that maintain the high standards RISD is known for.\n\n2. **Savannah College of Art and Design (SCAD)**: SCAD offers online programs that cover a wide array of design fields, including interior design, graphic design, and user experience design.\n\n3. **Parsons School of Design at The New School**: Known for its rigorous programs, Parsons offers online courses and certificates that are highly respected in the design community.\n\n4. **California Institute of the Arts (CalArts)**: CalArts offers a variety of online courses and programs in graphic design, motion design, and other creative fields through its Extended Studies program.\n\n5. **School of the Art Institute of Chicago (SAIC)**: SAIC offers a range of online continuing education courses that are well-regarded in the design world.\n\n6. **University of the Arts London (UAL) Online Short Courses**: UAL offers a variety of online short courses in different design disciplines, from fashion to graphic design to interior design.\n\n7. **Coursera and edX Platforms**: These platforms host design courses from top universities like Stanford, the University of Pennsylvania, and others, providing high-quality education opportunities in collaboration with leading institutions.\n\n8. **LinkedIn Learning**: Offers a wide range of design courses taught by industry experts, suitable for enhancing specific skills in graphic design, UX/UI, and more.\n\n9. **Skillshare**: Known for its practical approach, Skillshare offers numerous classes in various design disciplines taught by experienced professionals.\n\nWhen choosing an online design school, consider factors such as curriculum, faculty, accreditation, flexibility, networking opportunities, and cost. Check reviews and try to connect with alumni or current students to gauge the quality and relevance of the programs to your career aspirations.",
